<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>BAC Exam – Principles of Web Design</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=IM+Fell+English:ital@0;1&family=Source+Serif+4:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,600;0,700;1,400&family=DM+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  :root {
    --ink: #1a1410;
    --mid: #4a4540;
    --muted: #7a7570;
    --rule: #c8c0b4;
    --paper: #fdfaf5;
    --tint: #f5f0e8;
    --accent: #8b1a1a;
  }

  * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }

  body {
    background: #d4cfc7;
    font-family: 'Source Serif 4', Georgia, serif;
    color: var(--ink);
    padding: 30px 20px;
    font-size: 13px;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .exam-paper {
    background: var(--paper);
    max-width: 860px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 52px 64px;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.18), 0 0 0 1px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
    position: relative;
  }

  /* Margin line */
  .exam-paper::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 100px;
    top: 0;
    bottom: 0;
    width: 1px;
    background: rgba(200,150,150,0.3);
  }

  /* ── HEADER ── */
  .exam-header {
    text-align: center;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--ink);
    padding-bottom: 18px;
    margin-bottom: 22px;
  }
  .ministry {
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 2.5px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .exam-title {
    font-family: 'IM Fell English', serif;
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
  .exam-subtitle {
    font-family: 'IM Fell English', serif;
    font-size: 14px;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--mid);
  }

  /* Candidate info box */
  .candidate-box {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--ink);
    margin: 18px 0 24px;
    font-size: 11.5px;
  }
  .candidate-field {
    padding: 6px 10px;
    border-right: 1px solid var(--ink);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    display: flex;
    gap: 8px;
    align-items: baseline;
  }
  .candidate-field:nth-child(even) { border-right: none; }
  .candidate-field:nth-last-child(-n+2) { border-bottom: none; }
  .field-label {
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    white-space: nowrap;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .field-line {
    flex: 1;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    min-width: 80px;
  }

  /* Instructions box */
  .instructions {
    background: var(--tint);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    padding: 12px 16px;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
    font-size: 11.5px;
  }
  .instructions-title {
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 7px;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .instructions ol {
    padding-left: 18px;
    color: var(--mid);
  }
  .instructions ol li {
    margin-bottom: 3px;
  }

  /* Mark scheme row */
  .mark-scheme {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    margin-bottom: 28px;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
  }
  .mark-cell {
    flex: 1;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 5px 4px;
    border-right: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .mark-cell:last-child { border-right: none; }
  .mark-cell .sec { font-size: 8px; color: var(--muted); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1px; display: block; }
  .mark-cell .pts { font-size: 13px; color: var(--ink); font-weight: 500; }
  .mark-cell.total { background: var(--tint); }

  /* ── SECTION DIVIDER ── */
  .section-divider {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    margin: 28px 0 20px;
  }
  .section-divider::before,
  .section-divider::after {
    content: '';
    flex: 1;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--ink);
  }
  .section-tag {
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 9.5px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  /* ── QUESTION ── */
  .question {
    margin-bottom: 22px;
    page-break-inside: avoid;
  }
  .q-head {
    display: flex;
    gap: 12px;
    align-items: flex-start;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .q-num {
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--accent);
    background: rgba(139,26,26,0.07);
    border: 1px solid rgba(139,26,26,0.2);
    padding: 1px 7px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    white-space: nowrap;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 2px;
  }
  .q-marks {
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    color: var(--muted);
    white-space: nowrap;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 4px;
    margin-left: auto;
  }
  .q-text {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--ink);
    flex: 1;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .q-text strong { color: var(--accent); }

  /* Sub-questions */
  .sub-questions {
    margin-top: 8px;
    padding-left: 28px;
  }
  .sub-q {
    display: flex;
    gap: 10px;
    margin-bottom: 7px;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }
  .sub-label {
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--mid);
    font-weight: 500;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 20px;
    text-align: right;
    padding-top: 1px;
  }
  .sub-text {
    font-size: 12.5px;
    color: var(--ink);
    flex: 1;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .sub-marks {
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    color: var(--muted);
    flex-shrink: 0;
    padding-top: 2px;
  }

  /* Answer lines */
  .answer-lines {
    margin-top: 6px;
    padding-left: 28px;
  }
  .ans-line {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    height: 22px;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* Code snippet in question */
  .q-code {
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 11px;
    background: var(--tint);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--mid);
    padding: 8px 12px;
    margin: 8px 0 6px 28px;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--mid);
  }
  .q-code .kw { color: var(--accent); }
  .q-code .val { color: #1a5c2a; }
  .q-code .cm { color: var(--muted); font-style: italic; }

  /* MCQ options */
  .mcq-options {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 4px 20px;
    margin: 8px 0 4px 28px;
  }
  .opt {
    display: flex;
    gap: 8px;
    align-items: baseline;
    font-size: 12.5px;
  }
  .opt-letter {
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--mid);
    font-weight: 500;
    width: 16px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  /* Match table */
  .match-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 8px 0 4px 28px;
    width: calc(100% - 28px);
    font-size: 12px;
  }
  .match-table th {
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    color: var(--muted);
    padding: 4px 10px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ink);
    text-align: left;
  }
  .match-table td {
    padding: 5px 10px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    vertical-align: top;
  }
  .match-table .col-a { width: 30%; font-weight: 600; color: var(--ink); }
  .match-table .col-b { width: 15%; text-align: center; }
  .match-table .col-c { color: var(--mid); }

  /* True/False */
  .tf-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: 10px;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 4px 0 4px 28px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    font-size: 12.5px;
  }
  .tf-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .tf-check { font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px; color: var(--muted); }
  .tf-boxes {
    margin-left: auto;
    display: flex;
    gap: 12px;
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--muted);
  }
  .tf-box {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 4px;
  }
  .box { width: 14px; height: 14px; border: 1px solid var(--mid); display: inline-block; flex-shrink: 0; }

  /* Scenario box */
  .scenario {
    background: var(--tint);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    padding: 10px 14px;
    margin: 8px 0 6px 0;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--mid);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .scenario strong { font-style: normal; color: var(--ink); }

  /* Page footer */
  .page-footer {
    margin-top: 36px;
    padding-top: 12px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    color: var(--muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.8px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  /* Blank fill */
  .blank { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ink); display: inline-block; min-width: 100px; margin: 0 3px; }

  @media print {
    body { background: white; padding: 0; }
    .exam-paper { box-shadow: none; padding: 30px 40px; max-width: 100%; }
    .exam-paper::before { display: none; }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="exam-paper">

  <!-- HEADER -->
  <div class="exam-header">
    <div class="ministry">Ministry of Education &nbsp;·&nbsp; Department of Information Technology</div>
    <div class="exam-title">PRINCIPLES OF WEB DESIGN</div>
    <div class="exam-subtitle">End-of-Unit Examination &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp; Chapters 1 through 4</div>
  </div>

  <!-- CANDIDATE FIELDS -->
  <div class="candidate-box">
    <div class="candidate-field"><span class="field-label">Candidate Name</span><span class="field-line"></span></div>
    <div class="candidate-field"><span class="field-label">Date</span><span class="field-line"></span></div>
    <div class="candidate-field"><span class="field-label">Student Number</span><span class="field-line"></span></div>
    <div class="candidate-field"><span class="field-label">Class / Group</span><span class="field-line"></span></div>
  </div>

  <!-- INSTRUCTIONS -->
  <div class="instructions">
    <div class="instructions-title">General Instructions</div>
    <ol>
      <li>This paper contains <strong>four sections</strong> corresponding to Chapters 1–4. Attempt <strong>all questions</strong>.</li>
      <li>Write legibly in the spaces provided. Answers written outside the answer spaces will not be marked.</li>
      <li>The total marks for this paper are <strong>100</strong>. The marks for each question are shown in brackets.</li>
      <li>Time allowed: <strong>2 hours 30 minutes</strong>. No additional time will be given.</li>
      <li>Electronic devices, notes, and textbooks are <strong>not permitted</strong>.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  <!-- MARK SCHEME -->
  <div class="mark-scheme">
    <div class="mark-cell"><span class="sec">Section A</span><span class="pts">/ 25</span></div>
    <div class="mark-cell"><span class="sec">Section B</span><span class="pts">/ 25</span></div>
    <div class="mark-cell"><span class="sec">Section C</span><span class="pts">/ 25</span></div>
    <div class="mark-cell"><span class="sec">Section D</span><span class="pts">/ 25</span></div>
    <div class="mark-cell total"><span class="sec">Total</span><span class="pts">/ 100</span></div>
  </div>


  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════
       SECTION A — CHAPTER 1: HTML5
  ══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <div class="section-divider"><span class="section-tag">Section A &nbsp;·&nbsp; Chapter 1: HTML5 &nbsp;·&nbsp; [25 marks]</span></div>

  <!-- Q1: MCQ -->
  <div class="question">
    <div class="q-head">
      <span class="q-num">Q1</span>
      <span class="q-text">Which of the following best describes the purpose of the <strong>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</strong> declaration?</span>
      <span class="q-marks">[2]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="mcq-options">
      <div class="opt"><span class="opt-letter">A.</span> It defines the page title shown in the browser tab</div>
      <div class="opt"><span class="opt-letter">B.</span> It tells the browser which rules to use when rendering the document</div>
      <div class="opt"><span class="opt-letter">C.</span> It links an external CSS stylesheet to the HTML file</div>
      <div class="opt"><span class="opt-letter">D.</span> It sets the character encoding for the document</div>
    </div>
    <div class="answer-lines"><div class="ans-line"></div></div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q2: True/False -->
  <div class="question">
    <div class="q-head">
      <span class="q-num">Q2</span>
      <span class="q-text">Indicate whether each of the following statements is <strong>True</strong> or <strong>False</strong> by placing a tick (✓) in the correct box.</span>
      <span class="q-marks">[4]</span>
    </div>
    <div style="margin-top:8px;">
      <div class="tf-row"><span class="tf-check">i.</span><span>Void elements require both an opening and a closing tag.</span><div class="tf-boxes"><div class="tf-box"><div class="box"></div> True</div><div class="tf-box"><div class="box"></div> False</div></div></div>
      <div class="tf-row"><span class="tf-check">ii.</span><span>The <code>&lt;body&gt;</code> section is the container for descriptive meta-information about the document.</span><div class="tf-boxes"><div class="tf-box"><div class="box"></div> True</div><div class="tf-box"><div class="box"></div> False</div></div></div>
      <div class="tf-row"><span class="tf-check">iii.</span><span>HTML was originally proposed by Tim Berners-Lee at CERN in 1989.</span><div class="tf-boxes"><div class="tf-box"><div class="box"></div> True</div><div class="tf-box"><div class="box"></div> False</div></div></div>
      <div class="tf-row"><span class="tf-check">iv.</span><span>The W3C was founded to ensure that web standards are controlled by a single commercial vendor.</span><div class="tf-boxes"><div class="tf-box"><div class="box"></div> True</div><div class="tf-box"><div class="box"></div> False</div></div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q3: Fill in the blanks -->
  <div class="question">
    <div class="q-head">
      <span class="q-num">Q3</span>
      <span class="q-text">Complete the following sentences by writing the correct term in each blank.</span>
      <span class="q-marks">[5]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="sub-questions">
      <div class="sub-q"><span class="sub-label">i.</span><span class="sub-text">An HTML element that consists of only a single tag is called a <span class="blank">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> element.</span></div>
      <div class="sub-q"><span class="sub-label">ii.</span><span class="sub-text">The <span class="blank">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> provides extra information about an element and is written inside the opening tag.</span></div>
      <div class="sub-q"><span class="sub-label">iii.</span><span class="sub-text">HTML is an application of <span class="blank">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>, the Standard Generalized Markup Language.</span></div>
      <div class="sub-q"><span class="sub-label">iv.</span><span class="sub-text">CSS stands for <span class="blank">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>.</span></div>
      <div class="sub-q"><span class="sub-label">v.</span><span class="sub-text">The component in a browser that interprets and renders HTML is called the <span class="blank">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>.</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q4: Code analysis -->
  <div class="question">
    <div class="q-head">
      <span class="q-num">Q4</span>
      <span class="q-text">Study the HTML5 code snippet below and answer the questions that follow.</span>
      <span class="q-marks">[6]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="q-code">
<span class="kw">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span><br>
<span class="kw">&lt;html&gt;</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="kw">&lt;head&gt;</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="kw">&lt;title&gt;</span>My Page<span class="kw">&lt;/title&gt;</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="kw">&lt;link</span> <span class="val">href=</span><span class="cm">"styles.css"</span> <span class="val">rel=</span><span class="cm">"stylesheet"</span><span class="kw">&gt;</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="kw">&lt;/head&gt;</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="kw">&lt;body&gt;</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="kw">&lt;h1</span> <span class="val">id=</span><span class="cm">"main"</span><span class="kw">&gt;</span>Welcome<span class="kw">&lt;/h1&gt;</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="kw">&lt;p&gt;</span>Hello, World!<span class="kw">&lt;/p&gt;</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="kw">&lt;br&gt;</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="kw">&lt;/body&gt;</span><br>
<span class="kw">&lt;/html&gt;</span>
    </div>
    <div class="sub-questions">
      <div class="sub-q"><span class="sub-label">a.</span><span class="sub-text">Identify the <em>root element</em> in the code above.</span><span class="sub-marks">[1]</span></div>
      <div class="answer-lines"><div class="ans-line"></div></div>
      <div class="sub-q" style="margin-top:8px;"><span class="sub-label">b.</span><span class="sub-text">The <code>&lt;br&gt;</code> tag on line 10 is a void element. State what is meant by a <em>void element</em> and give one other example.</span><span class="sub-marks">[2]</span></div>
      <div class="answer-lines"><div class="ans-line"></div><div class="ans-line"></div><div class="ans-line"></div></div>
      <div class="sub-q" style="margin-top:8px;"><span class="sub-label">c.</span><span class="sub-text">The <code>&lt;link&gt;</code> element in the <code>&lt;head&gt;</code> references <em>styles.css</em>. Explain the purpose of this line and state the difference between the <code>&lt;link&gt;</code> tag and the <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> tag.</span><span class="sub-marks">[3]</span></div>
      <div class="answer-lines"><div class="ans-line"></div><div class="ans-line"></div><div class="ans-line"></div><div class="ans-line"></div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q5: Short answer -->
  <div class="question">
    <div class="q-head">
      <span class="q-num">Q5</span>
      <span class="q-text">List and briefly explain <strong>any four</strong> HTML5 semantic elements used for page structure.</span>
      <span class="q-marks">[8]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="answer-lines">
      <div class="ans-line"></div><div class="ans-line"></div><div class="ans-line"></div><div class="ans-line"></div>
      <div class="ans-line"></div><div class="ans-line"></div><div class="ans-line"></div><div class="ans-line"></div>
    </div>
  </div>


  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════
       SECTION B — CHAPTER 2: WEB DESIGN PRINCIPLES
  ══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <div class="section-divider"><span class="section-tag">Section B &nbsp;·&nbsp; Chapter 2: Web Design Principles &nbsp;·&nbsp; [25 marks]</span></div>

  <!-- Q6: Define -->
  <div class="question">
    <div class="q-head">
      <span class="q-num">Q6</span>
      <span class="q-text">Define the term <strong>W3C</strong> and state <strong>any three</strong> of its purposes in the context of web development.</span>
      <span class="q-marks">[4]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="answer-lines">
      <div class="ans-line"></div><div class="ans-line"></div><div class="ans-line"></div><div class="ans-line"></div><div class="ans-line"></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q7: Matching -->
  <div class="question">
    <div class="q-head">
      <span class="q-num">Q7</span>
      <span class="q-text">Match each term in Column A with its correct definition in Column B by writing the appropriate letter in the space provided.</span>
      <span class="q-marks">[5]</span>
    </div>
    <table class="match-table">
      <tr><th>Column A — Term</th><th>Answer</th><th>Column B — Definition</th></tr>
      <tr><td class="col-a">1. Screen resolution</td><td class="col-b"><div class="box" style="margin:auto;"></div></td><td class="col-c">A. The visual appearance, colors, fonts, and layout of a website</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="col-a">2. Browser cache</td><td class="col-b"><div class="box" style="margin:auto;"></div></td><td class="col-c">B. A layout that adjusts automatically to different screen sizes</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="col-a">3. Look and feel</td><td class="col-b"><div class="box" style="margin:auto;"></div></td><td class="col-c">C. Width and height of a screen measured in pixels</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="col-a">4. Flexible layout</td><td class="col-b"><div class="box" style="margin:auto;"></div></td><td class="col-c">D. Local storage of downloaded web files for faster repeat visits</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="col-a">5. CSS Media Query</td><td class="col-b"><div class="box" style="margin:auto;"></div></td><td class="col-c">E. A CSS technique for applying different styles to different devices</td></tr>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- Q8: Accessibility -->
  <div class="question">
    <div class="q-head">
      <span class="q-num">Q8</span>
      <span class="q-text">State and explain <strong>three</strong> accessibility features a web designer should consider when building a website.</span>
      <span class="q-marks">[6]</span>
